EngLawArticles.EngArticleContent:
After receiving applications for protection or notices of protection, the Rehabilitation Protection Association or its branch Association shall examine the needs of protected individuals and apply one or more temporal protection measures as follows:
1. Subsidizing traveling fees;
2. Helping to buy or supply transportation tickets;
3. Subsidizing the expense of lodgment and the meal;
4. Helping to make household registration;
5. Subsidizing the expense of medical cares;
6. Offering loans of small amount;
7. Others necessary protection measures.
